# Safety And Data Boundaries

## Non-negotiables

- Never commit secrets, API keys, or service-role tokens.
- Never expose server-only env vars to client bundles (`NEXT_PUBLIC_*` only for client-safe values).
- Treat any future API input as untrusted.

## Static site (current)

- No PII in repo content unless intentional marketing copy.
- External links (app login, card host) must use `src/lib/constants.ts` helpers where applicable.

## Future public endpoints

When adding `src/app/api/**`:

- Validate with explicit schemas (prefer Zod).
- Rate-limit public submission endpoints.
- Use Cloudflare Turnstile on lead forms.
- Return safe client errors; keep details in server logs only.
- No email/phone/name in logs.

## Analytics

- Do not add third-party tracking SDKs unless explicitly approved.
- First-party analytics (if added) must follow team privacy policy and AGENTS.md.
